claim: Flublok (quadrivalent) was evaluated in the pivotal trial against Fluarix (quadrivalent standard-dose vaccine).
explanation: Graphical figure with multiple panels showing hemagglutination inhibition (HI) titers (Log2 scale) at Day 0 and 1 month post-vaccination across two age cohorts (18–44 yrs and 45–64 yrs) and four influenza strains (A(H3N2), A(H1N1)pdm09, B/Victoria, B/Yamagata). Each panel displays box-and-whisker plots for six color-coded vaccine sequence groups: ccIIV4→ccIIV4, ccIIV4→RIV4, RIV4→ccIIV4, RIV4→RIV4, IIV4→ccIIV4, and IIV4→IIV4. The figure compares RIV4 and IIV4 generically but does not name Flublok or Fluarix; therefore, it does not support the claim that Flublok was evaluated against Fluarix. Note: Figure uses generic vaccine codes without brand names; resolution may limit visibility of any caption text specifying brands.
